President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Kurt Campbell as Deputy Secretary of State. Campbell currently serves as Deputy Assistant to the President and Coordinator for Indo-Pacific Affairs on the National Security Council. He has a distinguished career, having previously held positions such as founding Chairman and CEO of The Asia Group, Assistant Secretary of State for East Asian and Pacific Affairs, and CEO and Co-Founder of the Center for a New American Security. Campbell is also an author and has received numerous awards, including the Secretary of State's Distinguished Service Award.